<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Reveal" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Reveal,</orth> to disclose, to discover, to lay open: Lucr. Arg. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 85</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 1086" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1086</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 157</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.105" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.245" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 245</bibl>. Refl.: <cit><quote>r. yourself to him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 28</bibl></cit> (expound your case to him). <cit><quote>we still see them r. them-selves,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.27" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 27</bibl></cit> (betray themselves). <cit><quote>in complete glory she -- ed herself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.83" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 83</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>never --ed myself unto him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.192" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 192</bibl></cit>.
